ic.twitter.com/Z2rAZSear6](https://t.co/Z2rAZSear6)", "005-normal": "\u2014 CMO Odisha (@CMO\\_Odisha) [December 13, 2018](https://twitter.com/CMO_Odisha/status/1073032740432314368?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw)", "006-normal": "", "007-normal": "Madhu Babu Pension Yojana was launched in January 2008 by merging 2 pension schemes \u2013 Old Age Pension and Odisha disability pension yojana. All the beneficiaries get Rs. 300 p.m lying in the age group of 60 years to 79 years and Rs. 500 per month for people of 80 years of age or above. MBPY scheme also extends benefits to widows, leprosy and AIDS benefits.", "008-normal": "Unmarried women above 30 years of age who belongs to BPL family and has individual income below Rs. 24,000 per annum are also eligible under MBPY. This decision is going to put an additional burden of Rs. 60 crore for 4 months (December to March) of the current 2018-19."}}